{"word":"H1403 - גַּבְרִיאֵל - Gabrîyʼêl - gab-ree-ale' - Garbriel","slug":"H1403","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">גַּבְרִיאֵל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Gabrîyʼêl"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>gab-ree-ale'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Garbriel"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"Original: <b><he>גּבריאל</he></b> <p />Transliteration: <b>gabrı̂y'êl</b> <p />Phonetic: <b>gab-ree-ale'</b> <p class=\"bdb_def\"><b>BDB Definition</b>:</p> Gabriel = \"warrior of God\" or \" man of God\" <ol><li>an archangel; the angel God used to send messages of great importance to man; sent to Daniel, to Zacharias, and to Mary</li></ol> <p />Origin: from <a href=\"#/H1397\">H1397</a> and <a href=\"#/H410\">H410</a> <p />TWOT entry: None <p />Part(s) of speech: Proper Name Masculine "},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1368\">H1368</a>, <a href=\"#/H1369\">H1369</a>, <a href=\"#/H1376\">H1376</a>, <a href=\"#/H1377\">H1377</a>, <a href=\"#/H1396\">H1396</a>, <a href=\"#/H1397\">H1397</a>, <a href=\"#/H1398\">H1398</a>, <a href=\"#/H1399\">H1399</a>, <a href=\"#/H1402\">H1402</a>, <a href=\"#/H1404\">H1404</a>"}]}